<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for loop uses off as the single loop counter, but the third clause is off += (size_t) ret. The identifier ret is assigned inside the loop body (ret = send(...); and ret = 0 in the EAGAIN case), so the third clause uses an object that is modified in the loop body. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 (clause 3) which forbids the third clause from using objects modified by the loop body.
</scenario>
